<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,562,767]" pageId="9" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,569,598,623]" pageId="9" pageNumber="461">Note on availability and status.</emphasis>
The taxon name is hereby resurrected from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Prochazka, 1894" authorityName="Prochazka" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Danacea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[1248,1435,599,622]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="461">Danacea micans</emphasis>
Prochazka, 1894
</taxonomicName>
: The name of this taxon is deemed available and subspecific, because the work published before 1960 did not unambiguously indicate that the name was infrasubspecific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="461" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,562,767]" pageId="9" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,706,731]" pageId="9" pageNumber="461">Comments.</emphasis>
The original diagnosis clearly states that the specimen(s), on which the taxon is based, should possess a pronotum of different shape than in those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prochazka" authorityYear="1894" box="[761,875,743,766]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Danacea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[761,875,743,766]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="461">D. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
